Package org.lfj.lang.util

Class TypeDispatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lfj.lang.util.TypeDispatcher
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ManualTypeDispatcher, ReflectiveTypeDispatcher
    public abstract class TypeDispatcher
extends java.lang.Object
    A type dispatcher dispatches class member specs for its parameters. This can be used to handle reflection based upon both classes that are loaded and classes that are currently being defined. In certain cases it is necessary to get the member spec and not just the type of some class member like when determining if a declared method is private or not. If it is private then invokespecial can be used instead of invokevirtual for example.
